JO  - AMR
SP  - 313
EP  - 330
VL  - 12
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper suggests an integrative framework for research on consensus in strategy formulation?performance relationships. The proposed model has two components. First, a descriptive component explores the environment?consensus relationship in which the environment is conceptualized along the dimensions of munificence, complexity, and dynamism. Second, a normative component investigates the role that the match between environment, consensus, and integrating structure plays in explaining differences in organizational performance.
