TY  - JOUR
T1  - A New Perspective on Equity Theory: The Equity Sensitivity Construct
AU  - Huseman, Richard C.
AU  - Hatfield, John D.
AU  - Miles, Edward W.
Y1  - 1987/04/01
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1987.4307799
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1987.4307799
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 222
EP  - 234
VL  - 12
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Equity theory proposes that individuals who perceive themselves as either underrewarded or overrewarded will experience distress, and that this distress leads to efforts to restore equity. This paper describes a new construct, equity sensitivity, and proposes that reactions to equity/inequity are a function of an individual's preferences for different outcome/input ratios. The construct is delineated through a series of propositions, and implications for equity research in organizations are discussed.
AB  - Equity theory proposes that individuals who perceive themselves as either underrewarded or overrewarded will experience distress, and that this distress leads to efforts to restore equity. This paper describes a new construct, equity sensitivity, and proposes that reactions to equity/inequity are a function of an individual's preferences for different outcome/input ratios. The construct is delineated through a series of propositions, and implications for equity research in organizations are discussed.
